<font color="#FF0000">SW AND SPARROWHAWK</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 27 14:33:59 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My Grandfather was a Marine and a career New York City Police Officer (in the days when there were no &quot;cops&quot;). He taught me his moves, his skills, and his lessons from his life experiences. I can still move through the woods and not make a sound, though I am rusty these days and have to work at it.<br><br>
His training was borne of the deliberate methodology of application of stress. His reactions to danger were that intense look of concentration, the tightly coiled spring, the confident stance of doing things right the first time because you only get one chance. He taught me but did not explain.<br><br>
In Vietnam, I found myself clamped in situations that scared me literally out of my mind. Although I had no &quot;formal&quot; training, I reverted a state very much like I now recally seeing in my Grandfather. It is clear to me, though, that he had pulled himself up and out to one side over time. I was not so lucky. I had no training or support structure to do that. I stayed fixed in a timewarp set of endless loops in which I acted out the conduct of my life. I am at many levels, still in those loops. The support I receive now is training me to compensate.<br><br>
SW and Sparrowhawk,<br><br>
I can feel those things you discuss as if they were part of my personal experience. I consider myself lucky that I was spared the completely borderline lethal emotional intensity that some experienced, and from which many never emerged. Your words convey a point of view that is the concrete reality of life in the extreme, and sometimes beyond.<br><br>
It is important for people to realize these realities are not macho fantasies of vine swinging commando wannabees, but the awfull and very human truth of what it takes to win when you only have but that one chance.<br><br>
Thanks for posting your thoughts and experiences. I hope others will read them in the light of your motive for posting them, a motive of understanding.<br><br>
Art
